  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis index for a Class III VAD at Model Risk Level 5 during continuous-flow cardiac support at 5 L/min, 100 mmHg differential pressure, and hematocrit 40%. Monte Carlo UQ is performed across power-law hemolysis model coefficients. Seven of thirteen credibility factors are assessed; all achieved levels fall below required levels. Six factors remain unassessed due to epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted with conditions pending gap closure.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-powerlaw-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-2013",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-nib-benchmark-2019"
  ],
